               <msContents>
                  <summary>Private letter in which the writer seems to be discussing arrangements of some kind for a celebration (maybe funeral). He says the house is ready but complains of not having the appropriate items (sach as a vat, maybe a coffin, and a couch)</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers; on the verso, an address</note>
                     <note type="general">10 lines; broken on all sides</note>
                     <note type="general">The letters are well formed and written separately; some ligatures are used</note>
                     <note type="general">The text of the address is partly obscured by a heavy layer of dirt</note>
